                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hale</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1913</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your telegrams of November 11,
                    7 p.m., and November 26, 3 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">November 27</hi>],<note
                        n="34" xml:id="d897fn1">Not printed.</note> and to the Department’s telegram
                    of November 25 [<hi rend="italic">26, 3 p.m.</hi>]<note n="34" xml:id="d897fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note> the Department encloses herewith six copies of the
                    President’s speech of October 27, 1913, at Mobile, Alabama, in which relations
                    with Latin America are discussed with particular reference to the subject of
                    concessions. The question of oil concessions in Costa Rica is, however,
                    conceived to be of unusual interest because of its relation to naval bases and
                    the proximity of Costa Rica to the Panama Canal.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
